reviews.review_text: great recording brings back the full moon experience It was my friends birthday, the weather was perfect and when the Dead stopped playing and we all filed out... someone began howling at the moon.  And there we were - hundreds of Deadheads with our heads still twirling and full of music... standing in the street outside the Greek howling at the moon!  What a memory.

Of note: To Lay Me Down. Whatever rabbit Garcia pulls out of his hat for that solo on To Lay Me Down---just take a listen to the tune.  The audience will 100% confirm what is going on...

Any of these 81' Greeks will blow you away.  have fun!
